    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-06T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-06T19:00:00-05:00" n="431"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 763.72112Aml/38</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BJW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Belt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-06T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 2, 4 p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d431fn1">Not printed.</note> and
                    February 4, 11 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d431fn2">Not printed.</note> Text of note
                    of Honduran Government dated January 27, amended and corrected by your telegram
                    February 3,<note n="2" xml:id="d431fn3">See footnote 1, <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_383">p. 383</ref>.</note> was transmitted
                    to War Trade Board for its consideration. The guarantees of the Honduran
                    Government appear satisfactory and resumption of traffic to Amapala through
                    agent of Pacific Mail is approved.</p>
                <p>This information has been communicated to <persName>Rosseter</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
